io.odysz.semantic.jprotocol

Enum AnsonMsg.Port

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<AnsonMsg.Port>
      • io.odysz.semantic.jprotocol.AnsonMsg.Port
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    io.odysz.anson.IJsonable, IPort, Serializable, Comparable<AnsonMsg.Port>
    Enclosing class:
    AnsonMsg<T extends AnsonBody>

    public static enum AnsonMsg.Port
extends Enum<AnsonMsg.Port>
implements IPort
    Port is the conceptual equivalent to the SOAP port, the service methods' group.
    Client must use enum name, e.g. heartbeat, session in json. And url are explained at server side. NOTE: java code shouldn't use switch-case block on enum. That cause problem with generated class.
    Author:
    odys-z@github.com
